rComments: Honestly, Dr. Coates is one of my favorite professors. He's very engaging in class, makes an effort to put together a thoughtful lecture, and his exams are very fair. This was an online class when I took it and the exams were all open book with short and long answer questions. Such a funny, well thought out, and memorable class. 11/10

Amazing professor and person. His lectures are extremely engaging and he makes the effort to answer every student's question in and out of class. Would definitely recommend taking at least one of his classes if you get the chance.

I absolutely loved Professor Coates, he is the best. Super understanding and an amazing professor. Clearly communicates his expectations and instructions and really listens to his students. Has no concrete deadlines as long as they are handed in before the end of the semester. I loved Prof. Coates and 100% recommend taking a course with him

Honestly overall a good professor, but the amount of work required for the assignments was ridiculous. He does not give clear instructions. For the case formulation he expects us to be clinical psychologists. Honestly would rather have had two midterms and a final then all of the assignments. Way to much work. He is a nice person but not worth it.
teacherRatingTags: ['So many papers', 'Lots of homework', 'Accessible outside class']

rComments: I honestly loved Professor Coates I just hated the content of this class. Really hard to get into so I obviously did not attend and didnt do as well. I think there were 5 mini assignments (+ 2 optional ones), a midterm paper, and a take home final.

Can't say enough good things about professor Coates! Truly cares about his students, makes lectures very fun and interesting. Was very accommodating with the COVID situation in regards to due dates. By far one of the best profs at UofO!
Great prof, responds quickly to emails. Concerned about student wellbeing!! Gives amazing outlines for research paper and lots of help with it.

Dr. Coates is a really great professor who is passionate and very knowledgeable about clinical psychology. The Psychopathology course is content heavy, but professor Coates provides engaging examples and lectures. Marking is very clear and fair, and he is approachable outside of class. Great class and a very considerate professor!

Best psych prof I've had and one of the best profs I've had overall. His lectures are extremely interesting and the class discussions are super insightful. He's very caring and personable/easy to talk to. Makes you work hard for the grade but you really do end up taking a lot away from the class. Highly recommend!

Amazing prof, TAKE HIM. He is a pro at what he does and knows a lot about the material. His class was engaging and he'd give us some recommendations on books or crack some jokes. He even hosted a grad school info session. Midterm exam was easy but the final was really tricky & cumulative. Overall great class, just a lot of work needs to be invested

All the other reviews make sense, definitely some random/tricky MC questions, but as long as you study the slides extensively you should do well since the prof basically reads right off them! Two assignments (grade boosters), a midterm and cumulative final where the diagnostic questions ended up being easier than the MC.

He really tries to be enthusiastic about the content and make everyone participate. However, his exams and his grading is TOUGH. If you're expecting the actual "abnormal" part of this class, there isn't any. It's super boring and he does not talk about cases he has encountered.
The MC portion on his exams are very tough and wordy.
He is a very nice proff, who delivers very engaging lectures.  The MC portion on his exams are not easy.
great helpful best among all

Dr. Coates is an excellent prof. Really knows the course material and is a very engaging lecturer. Knows how to play off a bad questioncomments without making the person who asked feel stupid. Midterms and exam aren't easy. Could be a little more clear as to exactly what he'll be covering. Overall enjoyed the class.

Dr. Coates is definitely one of the best psychology professors at uOttawa. His lectures are so interesting and he makes them so funny through many examples and class discussion. His midterm is easy if you study and the assignments are grade boosters. He's always looking out for his students providing us with many resources. Recommend x100!

Excellent class! Topic is interesting and he really promotes class discussion so you get to learn about a lot of different experiences. You work hard for your marks but grading is fair and papers are actually really interesting and fun to do!!

GReat guy! prepared for class. explains things well and is willing to help outside of class. However, be WARNED! his test are tough. I think that he really goes out of his way to make sure the average is not too high.

Absolutely amazing prof - hands down one of my favorites! He makes the material super interesting and he marks very fairly. Make sure to attend his class not only because his lectures are interesting, but the added eye candy is a nice bonus. Def will be looking for another of his classes to take!

Best prof I've had so far! Engaging, works hard, clear expectations, and he is a very clear speaker! He is open-minded and approachable. The content is extremely interesting, and the in-class activities are fun. I'm going to miss this class next semester.

Excellent prof! Very inclusive classroom environment--respects everyone's opinion and ties irrelevant comments back to class content. Explains things very well and makes it interesting. Textbook and lecture notes are only good to reinforce his lectures. Love this prof!!

Makes class very interesting! Goes straight from slides so if you miss class, not a huge deal. His slide material is also all in the textbook. He thoroughly loves the subject matter and is very engaging.

Really nice guy, but not the most knowledgeable/ open minded person. Very biased to his own views, discounting and not even respecting theorists and trains of thought he doesn't agree with. Tests are fairly poorly written and he seems to think a bit too highly of himself (paper examples provided he wrote himself and tried to make them more advanced than what he expects, ironically poorly written btw) BUT an interesting lecturer, better than a lot of profs, I would recommend if other sectionssuck

Great prof! Organized, helpful, and lectures with great clarity! He makes class interesting - I could have read the textbook and never shown up, but I did because he explains it so well, I hardly had to read the textbook. TAKE HIS CLASS.
Took him for Social Psych. AWESOME prof. super smart/interested in his field and is SUPPERR friendly. exams reflect the material well and he is very clear with the info he teaches.

good prof, likes what he teaches and presents new studies and material as it becomes available  throughout the psych community. Exams and essays are straight forward and "easy", just make sure you attend every class and study every word in your notes. I didn't use the textbook that much but it may be worth buying for some. Great class overall
Amazing prof! His exams are really hard but the other evaluations even it out. He seems to truly care about his students and is very approachable.

Extremely dry lectures and a tough marker. Not one student received an A+ out of over 40 enrolled. Though he provides clear guidelines on what is expected in assignments, the marking does not reflect what is in the guidelines. Uses some subjective-response questions for midterm and final.
Good professor, knows how to teach. This course is all about how to write tests, and ironically, he is very bad at writing tests.

Very good professor!  So passionate about his subject.  His midterm was a little tough but if you study his slides and read a little extra in the textbook you will be fine.  He is also very organized with his material and what he expects.  Such an amazing professor and definitely recommended!!!
Very interesting, funny and good looking! He is very kind too and you can tell he cares about his students!

Very knowledgeable in this subject, will spend every minute of a 3 hour class going through a 25-slide slideshow because he has so much to elaborate on. Very nice guy and very interesting subject matter. Recommended!
he's definitely passionate about the subject which makes it that much more interesting. Very funny and always seems really happy. Midterm was more than fair, and yeah, he's very good looking!

Awesome prof, very nice and you can tell that he is really passionate about psychology. I appreicate his approach to discussions--open ended questions without calling anyone out. Also, as other people have mentioned, he is distractingly good looking.

Lectures were interesting,well organized and succinct.  We had two assignments(a reflection and an essay)that were reasonable in length.  The midterm consisted of m/c and short answer questions and was fair.  I don't want to detract from the fact that he is intelligent and lectures very well,but he is distractingly good looking.

I took his PSY 3171A class. Assignments and course material are reasonable in difficulty. I like that he never forces students to attend and discussions in class are open and not forced. He is always well-groomed and good-looking, and hence the hot rating.

very difficult class, but mark is extremely helpful in office hours.  the midterm was a shock, but with ALOT of hard work i managed to ace the final and the class.  i only used the text to clarify a couple of topics from his slides.  he made it fairly clear what the content of the final would be.
